reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 20, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Freezes with Phones. Does not Connect to Computers
reviews.reviewText: This was such a disappointing and frustrating experience. I spent 2 hours going through all of the different ways to connect it to my computer and phone and ultimately it would not connect with my computer no matter what I did and once I got it to work with my phone it would freeze up when I went to stream anything. This was not a phone or wifi issue as it was playing everything perfectly fine until I connected it to the projector. Super disappointed and a waste of money and now I am having a hard time returning it. DO NOT BUY!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 22, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars It was nice
reviews.reviewText: It was very nice for the 2 days it worked. After that it was awful. Sketchy 3rd party app that isn't on any app store, no pc support only phones, heated up quickly, focus ring wouldn't stay in place, would only connect via USB port, app would freak out before crashing, it would turn itself back on after turning off. Over all bad time, but the case of it is incredibly durable. Like it took 3 heavy swings with a mallet to get inside and pillage some goodies. Its made from nice parts and someone wanted this to be a good projector but the software is down right awful.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 15, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Good at nothing. Bad at everything else.
reviews.reviewText: Remote is spotty even right next to it. Speaker is vey very bad. Image quality is the worst I’ve ever seen, I couldn’t read text… of any kind. Airplay is buggy and presentations freeze. I guess you get what you pay for. If you’re getting it for a two year old to watch frozen, then I guess it’s not bad. But for what people want a compact projector for… this is not the one.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 24, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars An incredibly detailed portable mini projector!
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. FOSENHL mini projector has incredible detail for its small 4.33" x 3.54" x 1.96" size. Weighing in at only 0.55 oz makes this mini projector a true portable cinema. This is so FUN to watch and share with others, especially if you have a movie on your smartphone ( see my Video example). This way others can watch too and not crowd in to peek on to your smartphone. Love the cinema type projection, not the standard "box" look while watching movies.Projector comes with power cord ( although power bank hook up makes this truly portable) and instruction guide.Out of the box, setup was a breeze. Log into Wifi and set smartphone/laptop to accept wireless devices, such as this FOSENHL projector.Travel, camping, on-the-go and more makes this an incredible pleasure to have and enjoy movies and more with friends.Priced right makes this a no-brainer to have as a part of your entertainment collection. I'm glad our family ordered this and highly recommend it!
